\section{Open Questions}

Open questions need the prompt and a character limit, and they can optionally
carry a markdown fence language for uploaded file bodies.  The limit belongs to
the question data because it affects both the HTTP form and the canonical hash.
The fence hint also belongs here, but it has to be a single CommonMark info
word: whitespace or backticks would change the structure of the generated fence
rather than just its language tag.  We omit the hint from the canonical JSON
when it is unset so existing open-question hashes stay byte-for-byte stable.
The shared [[next]] and [[results]] flags shape the response flow; like every
presentation field they are stripped by [[canonical_dict]] before hashing, so
flipping either does not orphan the recorded answers.

<<classes>>=
