\subsection{Validation}

The two invariants protect the layers downstream.  An empty option set
has no ordering to ask for, and the form would render an empty control.
A [[top_n]] outside the closed interval $[1, |options|]$ is always an
authoring mistake: zero favourites asks for nothing, and a cap larger
than the option count can never be reached, so a respondent could never
produce a valid answer.  Checking at construction surfaces the typo when
the slide is compiled rather than when the first respondent loads the
form.

