\subsection{Building from image bytes}

[[from_image_bytes]] is the single place where image bytes meet the
question model.  Concentrating the I/O-adjacent work here keeps the
dataclass constructor pure --- the same property that lets
[[question_from_dict]] rebuild stored questions offline --- while
giving the authoring helpers a one-call path from a file's contents to
a registered question.

<<pin-image question methods>>=
@classmethod
def from_image_bytes(
    cls,
    text: str,
    data: bytes,
    *,
    image_path: str | None = None,
    max_pins: int = 1,
    allow_comment: bool = False,
    next: bool = True,
    results: bool | None = None,
) -> "PinImageQuestion":
    """Build a pin-image question from raw image bytes.

    The bytes are MIME-sniffed and hashed here, so the resulting
    object never needs filesystem access again.  Raises
    ``ValueError`` for bytes that are not an allowlisted raster
    format.
    """

    mime = sniff_image_mime(data)
    if mime is None:
        raise ValueError(
            "image data must be PNG, JPEG, GIF or WebP"
        )
    return cls(
        text=text,
        image_sha256=hashlib.sha256(data).hexdigest(),
        image_mime=mime,
        image_path=image_path,
        max_pins=max_pins,
        allow_comment=allow_comment,
        next=next,
        results=results,
    )
@

The central guarantee --- recompiling the same slide with the same
image is idempotent --- only holds if the path stays out of the digest.
We pin it by hashing the same bytes under two different paths.

